  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Canteens4Kids! Providing Eco-Friendly Alternatives</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In conjunction with our Responsible Schools: Environmental Education Program, this project will provide 8,000 STUDENTS in low-income California school districts with their very own reusable stainless-steel canteen, giving all children equal access to be part of the solution to disposable plastic pollution. We will fund the installation of eco-friendly, filtered, bottle-refill stations in 6 SCHOOLS,  encouraging students to make wholesome choices for their health and the environment.</narrative>
  </description>
